overview: The conversation began with the user requesting a detailed review of
  their sleep questionnaire application against the provided Statement of Work
  and a comprehensive questionnaire specification. The agent performed an
  initial assessment, identifying several critical gaps and missing features. A
  detailed plan was then created, outlining high, medium, and low priority
  action items. The agent proceeded to implement these items sequentially. Key
  implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with
  associated safety messaging, integrating detection logic for COMISA (Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, incorporating
  placeholder outbound links to relevant health resources in the generated
  reports, implementing a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS), expanding the CSV export functionality to include all
  questionnaire responses, and adding new questions for pain severity and
  chronic fatigue screening. The agent updated the application's types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic (both web and
  PDF) for each new feature.
